    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-01-08T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-01-08T00:00:00-05:00" n="509"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d509">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">611.573 Whale Oil/38</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum by the Secretary of State</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-01-08">January 8,
                            1936</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The Norwegian Minister called and renewed his interest in the whale oil tariff
                    revision by our Congress. I expressed equal interest in it and assured him that
                    we were giving the matter every attention and would be glad to keep him informed
                    as to developments. He then suggested what someone else had suggested last
                    summer after it was too late and that was the insertion of a provision in the
                    pending bill to the effect that whale oil imported to this country should be
                    inedible. His view was that that would be the only purpose of such imports in
                    any event, but that such insertion might disillusion some of the farmers who had
                    the erroneous impression this whale oil would compete with some of their edible
                    products, such as butter. I expressed interest in the suggestion and the
                    impression at the moment that it might be a wise and feasible step to take.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>C[<hi rend="smallcaps">ordell</hi>] H[<hi rend="smallcaps"
                        >ull</hi>]</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
